Bachelor of Engineering (B.E.) - First Degree Programmes

Apply at  https://admission.bits-dubai.ac.ae/

Engineering programmes are mathematics and hard science based that incorporate many up-to-date techniques of analysis and synthesis. These degree programmes are available with both Practice School and Thesis/Seminar options with a normal duration of 4 years.

By judicious choice of electives, students of any of these programmes can make themselves prepared for:

Admission to higher degree programmes in the best universities of the world.

Multi disciplinary, professional career, and much more.

A good career in teaching & research.

B.E. Biotechnology

Biotechnology Engineering is a part of engineering that involves the technology and biological science for development in the field of medical, agriculture, security and bio-research and much more

B.E. Chemical Engineering

Chemical engineering is the most versatile of engineering disciplines. No facets of modern civilization can be envisioned without contributions from chemical engineers. Through a judicious mix of mandatory and elective courses, the student at the Dubai campus gains expertise in various areas of chemical engineerings, such as petroleum and petrochemicals, textiles and synthetic fibers, colloids, suspensions, emulsions, etc.

B.E. Civil Engineering

Civil Engineering is instrumental in the country’s infrastructure as it deals with planning, design, construction, and maintenance of the built environment that improves mobility and convenience for the society. The graduates will have an option to work as design engineers, structural engineers, town planners, transport planners, environmental consultants, construction managers, and so on.

B.E. Computer Science

This programme helps the students to understand the various intricacies involved in computing technology. It focuses on the study of various topics such as languages, programming, algorithms, program designing and software designing.

B.E. Electronics & Communication Engineering

Electronics & Communication Engineering deals with the operating principles and design of devices ranging from mobile phone to wireless networks and satellite communication systems. This programme reflects the wide diversity of communication and data transmission technologies which are accepted as a vital part of everyday life.

B.E. Electrical & Electronics Engineering

This programme is a broad field that encompasses many sub-fields that deal with electrical power generation, transmission, distribution, protection of power system components against faults or abnormalities, solid-state electronics & allied fields.

B.E. Mechanical Engineering

Mechanical Engineering is the broadest of the engineering disciplines. In this programme, students learn to solve engineering problems in the area of design and manufacturing, automation, robotics and thermal-fluid engineering. Emphasis is on the process of learning and critical thinking to promote collaborative relationships with industries and other universities.

Eligibility Criteria For First Degree Programmes (B.E.)

The following eligibility criteria is applicable for admission to BITS Pilani, Dubai Campus. A candidate seeking admission to a particular programme has to meet the eligibility criteria for that programme as given below:



SCHOOL BOARDS 

CBSE    

ISCE  

CAMBRIDGE/EDEXCEL

IB 

MOE, UAE 

Any  other recognised State, National or International board



SUBJECT REQUIREMENTS 

Physics, Mathematics & Chemistry / Biology or any other vocational subject.

Physics, Biology and Chemistry or any other vocational subject(for Biotechnology only).



QUALIFYING EXAMINATION 

Grade 12 /A-Levels or its Equivalent



MINIMUM REQUIREMENTS 

Overall aggregate of 60% & minimum aggregate of 60% marks in Physics, Mathematics & Chemistry / Biology / Computer Science or any other vocational subject with minimum of 50% marks in each subjects.

 Eligibility Criteria for admission to First Degree Programmes

For admission to all first degree programmes, candidates must have passed the requisite qualifying examination, which is the General secondary education certificate examination of Ministry of Education, U.A.E. or All India senior school certificate examination of the Central Board of Secondary Education (CBSE) or A Level from Cambridge International examinations/ Edexcel or IB Diploma or its equivalent from any recognized State, National or International board.

The candidates must have obtained a minimum 60% overall aggregate of marks in the qualifying examination and a minimum aggregate of 60% in Physics, Mathematics and Chemistry/ Biology/ Computer Science or any other vocational subjects with at least 50% marks in each subject. However, for admission to B.E. Biotechnology, candidates without Mathematics in Grade 12 will also be accepted with a minimum aggregate of 60% in Physics, Biology and Chemistry or any other vocational subject with at least 50% marks in each subject.

If instead of marks any letter grades or GPA are awarded (or any other system of evaluation), their equivalences in marks will be decided by the Admissions Committee. If a Candidate has secured less than 50% marks in any one of these subjects – Physics, Mathematics /Biology, but has passed in the subjects and meets the aggregate criteria mentioned above, he/she may be considered for provisional admission. The admission will be confirmed only upon the successful completion of a foundation course in that subject with a minimum grade of ‘C’, offered by the institute preferably before the commencement of the first semester.

English is the medium of instruction and a good proficiency in English is essential for admission. Hence, candidates who have completed their qualifying examination from a Non-English medium school must have a TOEFL Score of 500 in paper based test or 61 in internet based test or have an IELTS Score of 6. If required, they may also be assessed by the Admission committee for English comprehension.

Department of Biotechnology 

Overview

Changes in economy towards science and technology require new profile of knowledge and skills to be incorporated into academic criteria. Globally, biotechnology represents a major driver for a high technology professional carreer. The demands from the biotechnology work force sector for development of knowledge and competencies were a major driving force for starting the B.E. Biotechnology program at BITS in the Middle East. The Department of Biotechnology established in the year 2007, offers B.E. Biotechnology & M.E. Biotechnology. It houses a total of six state of the art laboratories which are active in teaching and research. The main objectives of the department are 

Generating laboratory facilities for taking up R&D projects from various sponsoring agencies /industries

Strengthening the University linkage through R&D projects 

Conduct Hands on training for the faculty members and students in the field of Biotechnology.

Strengthening the B.E. Biotechnology and ME biotechnology program 

The department of biotechnology has collaboration with Department of Pathology, Uniformed Services University of Health Sciences, Bethesda, Maryland, USA for exchange of faculty and students, visit of experts and scientists between both the organizations and transfer of students to higher degree program. The department also collaborates with International centre for Biosaline Agriculture (ICBA) for engaging in R&D activities such as biosaline agriculture and biofertilizer development.  As a part of MoU there is a provision for Internship (PS) for students through short term and long term projects at both the institutes.

1. Why Parents /Students choose Biotechnology in BITS Pilani Dubai Campus?

Biotechnology and Biological Sciences Programs of BITS Pilani is ranked top 351-400 worldwide and top 11 in India.

Best Infrastructure for Engineering Program.

Biotechnology students are winning awards in prestigious international technical competitions organized by various authorities in UAE.

Ranked 5 star by KHDA Dubai.

Good Placements in reputed companies

Admission into top universities in the world for Higher Education. 

 

2. In What way Biotechnology courses are different from other Institutions or Universities?              

Regularly updated course curriculum as per the industry need.

Flexibility in choosing the course as per the required specialization of the student.

Project based learning of all the courses.

Creative evaluation methodologies for every course offered by the department.  

Practice School I and II (Industry Internship of seven and half months) for attaining industry experience before graduation.

On and Off-campus Thesis for students aiming research publications and aspiring to join league universities for Higher Education

3. In what way BITS Pilani Dubai Biotechnology Lab facilities, Faculty expertise is different from the other similar Institute in Dubai? 

100 % full time faculty are PhD holders from prominent universities.

Good research publications in leading International Journals. 

Faculty winning awards in the academic and research activities.

Department has well equipped lab with sophisticated equipment for good hands-on experience.



Department of Chemical Engineering

Overview

The Department of Chemical Engineering at BITS Pilani, Dubai Campus is one of the premier Chemical Engineering departments in the Gulf region. Offering undergraduate program since 2005, the department enrols students with exceptional calibre and to provide them with an environment in which they will grow intellectually and personally. The curriculum is distinctive in its emphasis on broad based education and direct intellectual engagement with faculty, a wide range of extracurricular opportunities, and the experience of living in a diverse campus community (Department brochure). 

Through a judicious mix of mandatory and elective courses, the  student at Dubai campus gains expertise in various areas of chemical engineering, apart from core chemical engineering principles, such as petroleum and petrochemicals, cement, ceramics and glass, polymers and plastics, Environmental pollution, corrosion, chemical process technology, Process plant safety, modelling and simulation in chemical engineering, colloids, suspensions, emulsions, etc. The department also tries to explore software like PYTHON, MATLAB, MINITAB, ASPEN HYSYS, PROMAX etc to the core courses.  

The department has collaborated in several research-based projects with prestigious organizations like IIT Guwahati, Shimadzu Middle-East and Africa, Dubai, BITS PILANI Goa Campus, International Centre for Biosaline Agriculture (ICBA), Dubai, Universitè de Toulouse, France, Ocean corner wastewater treatment and chemicals LLC, etc to name a few.                 

Why Chemical Engineering at BPDC?

1. Why  should Students choose Chemical Engineering in BITS Pilani Dubai Campus?

Chemical engineers solve the problems that affect our everyday lives by applying the principles of chemistry, physics, maths and biology.

Best Infrastructure with lab facilities to nurture both technical and lab-based knowledge.

Our students have participated in several competitions and won awards not only in the UAE but also in countries like Bahrain, India, Malaysia etc.

Ranked 5 star by KHDA Dubai.

The department engages students in approx. 7 months of internship (Practice School) in reputed companies in UAE 

·         Admission into top universities for the graduate students who tend to pursue higher studies. See our Student testimonials to know more.

2. In what way Chemical Engineering courses are different from other Institutions or Universities?              

Courses are designed to understand both industrial and computational aspects of Chemical Engineering

·         Interesting class-room session with STEM activities along with the usage of interactive panels 

Students get a chance to do Lab-project or Design project with the faculties of the department

The department also provides facilities for the students in the final year to do an Off-campus thesis with any university in the region or outside provided they have a faculty both in BPDC and the host university to agree upon the same. 

Practice school (PS) in reputed organizations in the UAE 

The department actively encourages the students to participate in different competitions, conferences and presentations of international standards 

3. What are the Faculty expertise and lab facilities available in the department 

All our faculties are PhD holders from world renowned universities with years of experience in research and teaching 

All faculties actively participate in research, resulting in journal papers, books, book chapters etc. in international publishing houses like Elsevier, Springer, Taylor & Francis

The department boasts of world class lab facilities to enhance the research aspect for each graduating student

4.      Research scenario in the department

·         The department has PhD scholars (Full time and Part time) who are actively engaged in research activities.

·       Undergraduate students are also actively encouraged to take up research projects. All the students of the department are made well accustomed with research equipment’s and research protocols which makes them a suitable candidate for future higher studies.



Department of Civil Engineering 

Overview

Civil Engineering is one of the oldest, broadest, and rapidly-growing disciplines of Engineering. Major sub-disciplines in Civil Engineering education are structural engineering, geotechnical engineering, transportation engineering, water resource engineering, construction technology and management, and environmental engineering. While the traditional side of civil engineering education focuses on structures, buildings and bridges, foundations, ports and waterways, energy and industrial facilities, and transportation, there is now a growing trend to branch into other areas of critical importance to society like futuristic transportation systems, sustainability of the built environment, smart cities, infrastructure management, disaster recovery, application of artificial intelligence and 3D printing of structures. These areas have also become important components of today’s Civil Engineering education. The upcoming decade will be challenging as well as an exciting time to choose civil engineering as the career, paving the path to improve the global quality of life on this planet.

 

Why Civil Engineering at BITS-Pilani, Dubai?

BITS Pilani-Dubai Campus introduced B.E. Civil Engineering program from the academic year 2016-17 to cater to the growing demands for Civil Engineers in Dubai. Over the years, the department has grown significantly with several graduated students being placed in reputed companies both in the Middle East and abroad. The department has also seen graduates pursuing higher degree programs in eminent international universities. The department offers a first-degree program with a modular academic structure. During the course of study, students are provided the option to enrol for electives in their area of interest, allowing them to explore a specialization in greater depth. Further, students can also opt to work on special projects during their course of study. The institute offers a unique 7.5-month internship program called practice school where significant time is spent working in the industry, thereby developing skills and gaining valuable experience. Candidates keen to pursue higher education are also encouraged to work on research-oriented projects as part of their final year thesis. The department also has collaborations with eminent professional bodies.

Department of Mechanical Engineering

Overview

Mechanical Engineering is the broadest of the engineering disciplines. Mechanical Engineers learn to solve engineering problems in the area of design and manufacturing, automation, robotics and thermal fluid engineering. BITS Pilani Dubai campus offers three tier structure of education i.e., BE in Mechanical Engineering, M.E. in Design Engineering and Ph.D in Mechanical Engineering. We educate the engineers of tomorrow by integrating class room teaching, laboratory experiments and hands-on projects. Emphasis is on the process of learning and critical thinking to promote collaborative relationships with industries and other universities. Students are exposed to work in professional environments through 30 weeks of Practice School (internship) programs in industries.

 

Mechanical Department hosts student chapters of various professional bodies such as Mechanical Engineering Association (MEA), American Society of Mechanical Engineers (ASME), Society of Automotive Engineers (SAE), American Society of Heating, Refrigeration and Air Conditioning Engineers (ASHRAE) and BITS Aerospace Society (BAEROS). Through these associations, students get introduced to current research and trends in different engineering disciplines.

Refund Policy

One-Time fee: 

Application fee and Admission Fee are non-refundable.

Activity fee is fully refundable if the student withdraws before the date of registration. If the student withdraws within four weeks from the date of registration, whether the student registers or not, 75% of the Activity fee is refundable. If the student withdraws after four weeks from the date of registration, the entire Activity fee is non-refundable.

Tuition Fee: 

If a student accepts the admission offer and completes the admission formalities but withdraws before the date of registration, 80% of the first installment of first semester tuition fee is refundable.

If a student withdraws within one week of the date of registration irrespective of whether the student registers or not, 50% of the first installment of first semester tuition fee is refundable.

If a student withdraws after one week of the date of registration irrespective of whether the student registers or not, the first installment of first semester tuition fee is non- refundable.

Hostel Fee: 

If a student opts not to avail the hostel facility after paying the hostel fee and if the request for the same is received before the commencement of the semester, 90% of the semester’s hostel fee and facility fee is refundable.

If request for not availing the hostel facility is received within one week of the commencement of the semester, 50% of the semester’s hostel fee and facility fee is refundable.

If request for not availing the hostel facility is received after one week of the commencement of the semester, the entire first semester’s hostel fee and facility fee is non-refundable.

Visa and Medical Insurance fee: 

a) Visa fee and Medical Insurance fee is non-refundable, if the same has been applied.

Transport Fee: 

If a student opts not to avail the transport facility after paying the transport fee and if the request for the same is received before the commencement of the semester, 90% of the semester’s transport fee paid is refundable.

If request for not availing the transport facility is received within two weeks of the commencement of the semester, 50% of the semester’s transport fee is refundable.

If request for not availing the transport facility is received after two weeks of the commencement of the semester, the entire first semester’s transport fee is non refundable.

Note: All refunds will take a minimum of 4 weeks from the date of withdrawal.

1.	Other Special Concessions 

a.	For GCC/Arab Nationals

Meritorious GCC/Arab Nationals may be offered a concession of up to 100% on the tuition fee for the normal duration of the programme (8 Semesters) based on their performance in the qualifying examination (Grade 12 or equivalent) for the first year and continuity of a minimum CGPA of 6.00 on a 10.00 scale for the subsequent semesters during the programme. These concessions will be restricted to specific number of students.

b.	For sudden bereavement of earning member of the family

The Institute helps such students by waiving off 100% tuition fee for a semester for those students who face financial hardships due to the sudden and untimely demise of the sole earning member of their family in that semester. A concession of up to 75% can be offered in the subsequent semesters, on a case to case basis, depending on means and need.

c.	For physically challenged students

All physically challenged students satisfying the conditions laid out are given a 15% concession on the tuition fee throughout the programme subject to satisfactory academic performance in each semester.

d.	For sibling

For families that have more than one child enrolled concurrently, a concession of 25% on the tuition fee is offered to the second child until the first child graduates.

e.	Scholarship for Sports Excellence 

a.	ENTRY LEVEL: Students who have participated and won medals in International championship by representing their Country are given scholarship of 50% of the first year tuition fee and students who have participated in the International Championships are given scholarships of 20% of first year tuition fee. The Sport and the eligibility criteria of all applicants will be evaluated on a case by case basis and the scholarship will be awarded based on committee’s recommendation.

b.	CONTINUING STUDENTS: Students who participate and win in three inter-university tournaments at the end of one academic year will be considered for a scholarship of 20% of tuition fee for the current year for the normal duration of the programme based on committee’s recommendation.
